(213, 1, '2025-10-17 17:37:57', '2025-10-17 17:37:57', '<div class=\"container\">\r\n<div class=\"breadcrumbs\">\r\n<div>\r\n<h3>About Us</h3>\r\n<a href=\"index.html\">Home</a> / About Us\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<section class=\"about-header\">\r\n<h1>About CIPIT</h1>\r\nThe Centre for Intellectual Property and Information Technology Law (CIPIT)\r\n\r\n</section><section class=\"about-section\">\r\n<h3>Who We Are</h3>\r\n<div class=\"about-content\">\r\n\r\nThe Centre for Intellectual Property and Information Technology Law (CIPIT) is an evidence-based research and training Centre based at Strathmore University, Nairobi, Kenya. Our mission is to study, create, and share knowledge on the development of intellectual property and information technology, especially as they contribute to African Law and Human Rights.\r\n\r\nOur team is multidisciplinary, drawn from law, political science, computer science and development, and uses diverse methodological approaches to inform debates on Information and Communications Technology (ICT) applications and regulation and educate and influence relevant stakeholders on attendant Intellectual Property (IP) and human rights issues.\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n</section><section class=\"about-section\">\r\n<h3>Our Mission &amp; Vision</h3>\r\n<div class=\"mission-vision\">\r\n<div class=\"card\">\r\n<h4><i class=\"fas fa-bullseye\"></i> Our Mission</h4>\r\n<p>To provide a critical and in-depth understanding of the laws and policies on intellectual property and information technology through the promotion of scholarship, research and training in the field.</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"card\">\r\n<h4><i class=\"fas fa-eye\"></i> Our Vision</h4>\r\n<p>To be the leading research and training Centre in the field of intellectual property and information technology in the Global South.<p>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</section></div>', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '91-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-10-17 17:37:57', '2025-10-17 17:37:57', '', 91, 'https://cipit.revamp.org.test/?p=213', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(214, 1, '2025-10-17 17:38:48', '2025-10-17 17:38:48', '        <!-- Work Header -->\r\n        <section class=\"work-header\">\r\n            <!-- Updated header content -->\r\n            <h3>Our Research & Impact Areas</h3>\r\n            <p>We focus on critical intersections of technology, law, and development, providing evidence-based research\r\n                and policy engagement across several key themes that shape the future of Africa\'s digital economy.</p>\r\n        </section>\r\n\r\n        <!-- Work Themes Section -->\r\n        <section class=\"work-themes-section\">\r\n            <h2>Core Research Pillars</h2>\r\n            <div class=\"themes-grid\">\r\n                <!-- Work Theme Card 1: Artificial Intelligence -->\r\n                <div class=\"work-theme-card\">\r\n                    <div class=\"work-theme-icon\">\r\n                        <i class=\"fas fa-brain\"></i>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"work-theme-content\">\r\n                        <h3>Artificial Intelligence</h3>\r\n                        <p class=\"theme-focus\">Policy Research & Ethics</p>\r\n                        <p>Analyzing the legal and ethical implications of AI adoption in Kenya and Africa, focusing on\r\n                            fairness, accountability, and transparency in deployment across various sectors.</p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <!-- Work Theme Card 2: Data Governance & Policy -->\r\n                <div class=\"work-theme-card\">\r\n                    <div class=\"work-theme-icon\">\r\n                        <i class=\"fas fa-database\"></i>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"work-theme-content\">\r\n                        <h3>Data Governance & Policy</h3>\r\n                        <p class=\"theme-focus\">Regulatory Frameworks</p>\r\n                        <p>Investigating local and cross-border data flows, developing policy recommendations for data\r\n                            protection, digital sovereignty, and privacy rights in the digital age.</p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <!-- Work Theme Card 3: Digital Identity -->\r\n                <div class=\"work-theme-card\">\r\n                    <div class=\"work-theme-icon\">\r\n                        <i class=\"fas fa-fingerprint\"></i>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"work-theme-content\">\r\n                        <h3>Digital Identity</h3>\r\n                        <p class=\"theme-focus\">Rights & Inclusion</p>\r\n                        <p>Researching the legal frameworks governing digital identity systems, their impact on\r\n                            inclusion\r\n                            and exclusion, and associated human rights concerns for vulnerable populations.</p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <!-- Work Theme Card 4: IP and Innovation -->\r\n                <div class=\"work-theme-card\">\r\n                    <div class=\"work-theme-icon\">\r\n                        <i class=\"fas fa-lightbulb\"></i>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"work-theme-content\">\r\n                        <h3>IP and Innovation</h3>\r\n                        <p class=\"theme-focus\">Commercialization Support</p>\r\n                        <p>Providing analysis on patent law, copyright, trademarks, and how to create an effective legal\r\n                            environment for technology transfer and innovation in the region.</p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <!-- Work Theme Card 5: Cyber Law & Policy -->\r\n                <div class=\"work-theme-card\">\r\n                    <div class=\"work-theme-icon\">\r\n                        <i class=\"fas fa-shield-alt\"></i>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"work-theme-content\">\r\n                        <h3>Cyber Law & Policy</h3>\r\n                        <p class=\"theme-focus\">Security & Legislation</p>\r\n                        <p>Focusing on national cybersecurity legislation, combating cybercrime, and the legal\r\n                            challenges\r\n                            posed by digital security threats, surveillance, and critical infrastructure protection.</p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n                <!-- Work Theme Card 6: Digital Trade & E-commerce -->\r\n                <div class=\"work-theme-card\">\r\n                    <div class=\"work-theme-icon\">\r\n                        <i class=\"fas fa-globe-africa\"></i>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                    <div class=\"work-theme-content\">\r\n                        <h3>Digital Trade & E-commerce</h3>\r\n                        <p class=\"theme-focus\">Market Access & Regulation</p>\r\n                        <p>Examining legal and policy issues related to digital trade agreements, consumer protection,\r\n                            and the regulatory environment for cross-border e-commerce in Africa.</p>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n', 'Our Work', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '95-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-10-17 17:38:48', '2025-10-17 17:38:48', '', 95, 'https://cipit.revamp.org.test/?p=214', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(215, 1, '2025-10-17 19:10:51', '2025-10-17 19:10:51', '<p>[vc_row][vc_column][vc_tta_tour][vc_tta_section title=\"Intellectual Property and Innovation Research\" tab_id=\"1731680586313-5d5c7fb5-0dab\"][vc_column_text css=\"\"]</p>\n<h4>Intellectual Property and Innovation Research</h4>\n<p>In an era of rapid technological advancement, the intersection of intellectual property (IP) and innovation plays a pivotal role in shaping economies and societies. Our Intellectual Property and Innovation research delves into the evolving landscape of IP laws, policies, and practices, with a particular focus on emerging technologies and industries.</p>\n<p>Our research provides in-depth analysis and insights into how IP frameworks can support innovation while balancing the rights and interests of creators, businesses, and the public. We explore a wide range of issues, including patent law, copyright, trademarks, trade secrets, geographical indications, traditional knowledge, and traditional cultural expressions. We place a special emphasis on their impact on the digital technology, creative industries, and biotechnology sectors.</p>\n<p>We provide evidence-based research and impartial analysis to support ongoing discussions on IP policy development at local, national, and continental levels. Our objective is to foster economic growth, safeguard creative and innovative endeavours, and ensure that IP policies are responsive to the challenges of an increasingly globalized and digital world.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"Section 2\" tab_id=\"1760728074134-74fe9f22-2060\"][/vc_tta_section][/vc_tta_tour][/vc_column][/vc_row]</p>\n', 'Artificial Intelligence', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '181-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-10-17 19:10:51', '2025-10-17 19:10:51', '', 181, 'https://cipit.revamp.org.test/?p=215', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(216, 1, '2025-10-17 19:12:26', '2025-10-17 19:12:26', '<p>[vc_row][vc_column][vc_tta_tour][vc_tta_section title=\"Intellectual Property and Innovation Research\" tab_id=\"1731680586313-5d5c7fb5-0dab\"][vc_column_text css=\"\"]</p>\n<h4>Intellectual Property and Innovation Research</h4>\n<p>In an era of rapid technological advancement, the intersection of intellectual property (IP) and innovation plays a pivotal role in shaping economies and societies. Our Intellectual Property and Innovation research delves into the evolving landscape of IP laws, policies, and practices, with a particular focus on emerging technologies and industries.</p>\n<p>Our research provides in-depth analysis and insights into how IP frameworks can support innovation while balancing the rights and interests of creators, businesses, and the public. We explore a wide range of issues, including patent law, copyright, trademarks, trade secrets, geographical indications, traditional knowledge, and traditional cultural expressions. We place a special emphasis on their impact on the digital technology, creative industries, and biotechnology sectors.</p>\n<p>We provide evidence-based research and impartial analysis to support ongoing discussions on IP policy development at local, national, and continental levels. Our objective is to foster economic growth, safeguard creative and innovative endeavours, and ensure that IP policies are responsive to the challenges of an increasingly globalized and digital world.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][vc_tta_section title=\"The Right to Research and Copyright Law: Text and Data Mining\" tab_id=\"1688724647906-c3840df5-7bc6\"][vc_column_text css=\"\"]</p>\n<h4>The Right to Research and Copyright Law: Text and Data Mining</h4>\n<p>Text and Data Mining (TDM) technology is a valuable tool in research, enabling the analysis of large amounts of data quickly. TDM involves a four-step process of identifying relevant documents, converting them to machine-readable format, extracting structured data, and mining the data for new knowledge. However, conducting research using TDM in Kenya presents several challenges, such as the absence of a supportive legal framework, limited access to reliable internet connections, a shortage of AI experts, and insufficient financial resources. TDM research often involves the use of copyrighted materials, requiring either consent from the copyright owners or exceptions in copyright law. While some countries have amended their laws to provide specific exceptions for TDM, Kenyas copyright law lacks clarity in this regard. Kenyas copyright framework has an exception for scientific research, but there is a lack of clarity on whether TDM research falls under this exception. Comparisons with South Africas copyright amendment law highlight the need for more specific and flexible exceptions. This research found that Kenyas copyright exceptions and limitations should be updated and expanded to accommodate TDM research and other technology-based research. International guidelines are also needed to address the application of copyright to TDM technology. Read more on our research findings and recommendations in this Policy Brief and White Paper.[/vc_column_text][/vc_tta_section][/vc_tta_tour][/vc_column][/vc_row]</p>\n', 'Artificial Intelligence', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '181-revision-v1', '', '', '2025-10-17 19:12:26', '2025-10-17 19:12:26', '', 181, 'https://cipit.revamp.org.test/?p=216', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
